properties.Name: CreditCardPayment
properties.Description: A payment made by the consumer upon the associated credit card account.

Columns.Name: PaymentCardId
Columns.Description:
Primary Account Number (PAN) = The number that is embossed, encoded, or both, on a plastic card that identifies the issuer and the particular cardholder account.

The account number on the card, which is unique to every cardholder. The card number is used to identify the purchaser for authorization and billing purposes.

Columns.Name: CreditCardPaymentDate
Columns.Description: The date that the credit card payment was made.

Columns.Name: PaymentDueDate
Columns.Description: The date that the payment is due.

Columns.Name: CreditCardTotalOutstandingAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of outstanding balance on the credit card as of the payment date.

Columns.Name: CreditCardMinimumPaymentDueAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of minimum payment that must be made on the credit card as of the payment date.

Columns.Name: CreditCardPaymentAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of payment made on the associated date.

Columns.Name: PaymentPeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period starting date for which the associated payment is applied.

Columns.Name: PaymentPeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period ending date for which the associated payment is applied.

Columns.Name: PaymentStatusId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a payment status.

Columns.Name: BillingCycleId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Billing Cycle.

Columns.Name: AccountStatusIdPriorToPayment
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Account Status prior to payment.

Columns.Name: AccountStatusIdPriorAfterPayment
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Account Status after payment.

Columns.Name: PaymentTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Payment Type.
